comment_regular_data.body:
@justinmk 
> Needs a rebase, and a test. And hopefully the code will be much simpler after removing the attempt to "guess" when the user cancels.

I removed the simplified guessed result, so the error handling is now moved outside linematch_nbuffers. I stored the failed state in diff_T.is_linematched, which is now an integer. 0: not yet ran, 1: success, -1: canceled. I'm not sure in the lua test how to simulate the ctrl-c press of the user to cancel it while it is still running.
